quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  17,31,"And do not kill your children for fear of poverty, We provide for them and for yourselves (too). Killing them is certainly a great mistake"
  17,32,"And do not (even) go near adultery, it is certainly indecent and an evil way"
  17,33,"And do not kill any person, whose (killing) God has made unlawful except (when his killing is) for the right (cause). And whoever is killed unjustly, then We have given authority to his heir, so let his (heir) not exceed the limits in killing (because) he is helped (by the law)"
  17,34,"And do not go near the wealth of an orphan, except in (a manner) which is the best, till he reaches his (age of physical and mental) strength. And fulfill the agreement, (you will) certainly be questioned (about) the agreement you had made"
  17,35,"And give back in full, the measure which you measure, and weigh with a balance that is straight. That is good and best (from the point of view of) the result"
  17,36,"And do not follow that about which you do not have (any) knowledge, the hearing and the sight and the heart, regarding each of those (you) will certainly be questioned"
  17,37,"And do not walk proudly in the earth, you can neither tear the earth nor can you ever reach the mountains in height"
  17,38,The evil of all that (which is mentioned above) is disliked by your Lord
  17,39,"That is from what your Lord has communicated to you of wisdom. And do not set up another god with God, lest you should be put in hell, blamed, driven away"
  17,40,Then has your Lord selected sons for you and He has (Himself) taken daughters from among the angels? You certainly utter a greatly( dreadful )saying